  • If you are using large quantities of Domestic LPG, consider converting to bulk tanks rather than using cylinders. Discuss your requirements with the approved contractor and the Contract Manager.
  • Save money on delivery costs in regional areas by picking up cylinders from the contractor's depot. Make sure you have an appropriate vehicle.

column2: Shipping Service - Fremantle, Broome and Wyndham Ports
column11:
• A regular coastal shipping service from Fremantle to the North of Western Australia.
  • The service currently operates on a 17 day rotation schedule calling at Fremantle, Broome & Wyndham ports.
  • Inland areas can also be accommodated through a door to door service. The Contractor utilises their own transport companies at the ports to call to reach local and regional inland destinations.
  • Note that the Contractor's objective is to sustain a commercially viable service and will consider increasing the schedule of ports to call where there is a reasonable demand for the service.
  • The vessel can carry all types of sea freight cargo; containers, bulk, break-bulk (motor vehicles, project cargo, machinery etc).
  • This shipping service is subsidised by the State Government of Western Australia.

Government Buyers must procure in accordance with State Supply Commission Policies.

  • Lodge your mail at the Australia Post lodgement centre you nominated on your Account Establishment Form.
  • Include a completed Mailing Statement whenever you lodge your mail.
  • Envelopes that show a typed address, particularly window-faced envelopes, are classified as "Clean Mail" and are discounted (eg. from 58c to 53.5c for small letters). Make sure you identify Clean Mail items on your mailing statement.
  • If you have large mail outs then consider bar-coding your addresses. This can reduce postage costs significantly (e.g. from 58c to 43.2c for small letters).
  • Postage costs vary with the size of the envelope. Fold A4 documents in thirds and insert into standard sized Government window-faced envelopes to obtain the lowest pricing. Double sided printing will make it easier to fold your letters.
  • Send non-urgent parcels through the post instead of using the Metro Courier CUA or the Freight CUA.

  • Use a whole of life calculator to compare the costs of various vehicles.

column24:
• Prices from the top to the bottom of the weekly price cycle can differ by 13 cents per litre for unleaded petrol. Thursdays are generally most expensive and prices decrease over the week being lowest on Wednesdays.
  • Top up your fuel tank when prices are cheap, don't just fill up when your tank is empty.

column24:
• Buy travel online using CWT's Online Booking Tool (OBT).
  • Do not have airline preferences.
  • Avoid "fully flexible" fares - discounted airfares should have the flexibility you need.
  • Buy the cheapest fare that meets your travel needs ("Best Fare of the Day").
  • Use any ticket credits early (they only last 12-months).
  • Streamline internal approval processes so that you can buy airfares early (the cheapest fares sell first).
  • Seek training and assistances from CWT.
  • Analyse your travel performance and change your buying behaviour as necessary.
